    <h1>Contributors User Manual</h1>

    <h2>Introduction</h2>
    <p>
        This page provides you with access to different tabs that categorize contributors based on their status. You can easily navigate between the tabs to manage and track the contributors' progress. Below are the four available tabs:
    </p>

    <h3>Contributors Waiting For Approval</h3>
    <p>
        This tab displays the contributors who are awaiting approval. The following columns are shown for each contributor:
    </p>

    <h4>Columns:</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>
            + (Expand): Clicking the "+" button to the left of Contributor ID expands to display additional columns:
            <ul>
                <li>RecordingID: Unique identifier for the recording.</li>
                <li>Transcript: Transcript associated with the recording.</li>
                <li>Recording Date: Date when the recording took place.</li>
                <li>RetryCount: Number of times the contributor attempted the recording.</li>
                <li>Comment: Additional comment or note about the recording.</li>
                <li>Actions: Available actions for the recording.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>ContributorID</li>
        <li>FirstName</li>
        <li>LastName</li>
        <li>Email Address</li>
        <li>Register Date</li>
        <li>HelperEmail</li>
        <li>Comments</li>
        <li>Actions (View Rating)</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Functionality:</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>
            <p>
                When you click "View Rating" in the Actions column for a specific contributor, a pop-up window appears, displaying the following information:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>Contributor ID: The unique identifier of the contributor.</li>
                <li>Name: The full name of the contributor (concatenation of the first name and last name).</li>
                <li>Rating: The rating associated with the contributor, indicating their performance or contribution level.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>Close Pop-up: To close the pop-up window, simply click the "X" (cross) button.</li>
        <li>Search Bar: Utilize the search bar to filter the results based on your search criteria.</li>
        <li>Default Entries: By default, the table displays 100 entries.</li>
    </ul>
    <img src="~/images/contributor-1.png" />

    <h3>Approved Contributors</h3>
    <p>
        This tab displays the approved contributors and their associated information.
    </p>

    <h3>Columns:</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>View Blocks: Clicking the plus (+) sign button expands the contributor's blocks.</li>
        <li>ID: Unique identifier for the contributor.</li>
        <li>FirstName: First name of the contributor.</li>
        <li>LastName: Last name of the contributor.</li>
        <li>ApprovedDate: Date when the contributor was approved.</li>
        <li>#Blocks: Number of blocks associated with the contributor.</li>
        <li>LastRecording: Date and time of the last recording by the contributor.</li>
        <li>AnnotatorAssigned: Whether an annotator is assigned to the contributor (Yes/No).</li>
        <li>Sent FollowUp Date: Date when a follow-up was sent to the contributor.</li>
        <li>Actions: Available actions for the contributor.</li>
    </ul>

    <img src="~/images/contributor-2.png" />

    <h3>Actions:</h3>
    <p>
        Depending on the context, the available actions may vary. Here are the actions explained:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>
            Assign Annotators: Allows you to assign annotators to the contributor's blocks for review and rating.
        </li>
        <img src="~/images/contributor-3.png" />
        <br />
        <li>
            View SIT Rating
        </li>
        <img src="~/images/contributor-4.png" />
        <br />
        <li>
            Send Follow-up: Enables you to send a follow-up communication to the contributor.
        </li>
        <img src="~/images/contributor-5.png" />
        <br />
    </ul>
    <h3>Expandable Rows:</h3>
    <p>
        Clicking the plus (+) sign button under the View Blocks column expands the contributor's blocks, displaying the following columns:
    </p>

    <ul>
        <li>Block: The block number.</li>
        <li>Actions: Available actions for the block.</li>
    </ul>
    <ul>
        <li>
            View Prompts: Lets you view the prompts associated with the specific block.
        </li>
        <img src="~/images/contributor-6.png" />
        <br />
        <li>
            View Recording: Allows you to listen to the recording associated with the specific block.
        </li>
        <img src="~/images/contributor-7.png" />
        <br />
        <img src="~/images/contributor-8.png" />
        <br />
        <li>
            View Rating: Allows you to view the rating associated with the specific block.
        </li>
    </ul>
    <h3>Non-Responsive Contributors</h3>
    <p>
        This tab displays the non-responsive contributors and their associated information.
    </p>

    <h4>Show entries:</h4>
    <p>
        Use this option to choose how many contributors you want to display per page.
    </p>

    <h4>Search:</h4>
    <p>
        Use the search bar to find specific contributors based on their ID, first name, last name, or email address.
    </p>

    <h4>Columns:</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>ID: Unique identifier for the contributor.</li>
        <li>FirstName: First name of the contributor.</li>
        <li>LastName: Last name of the contributor.</li>
        <li>Email Address: Email address of the contributor.</li>
        <li>Register Date: Date when the contributor registered.</li>
        <li>Comments: Additional comments or notes about the contributor.</li>
        <li>Sent FollowUp Date: Date when a follow-up was sent to the contributor.</li>
        <li>Actions: Available actions for the contributor.</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Actions:</h4>
    <p>
        Depending on the context, the available actions may vary. Here is the action explained for the 'Non-Responsive Contributors' page:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>
            View Rating: Allows you to view the rating associated with the specific contributor.
        </li>
    </ul>

    <img src="~/images/unresponsive_contributor-1.png" />
    <br />

    <h3>Denied Contributors</h3>
    <p>
        This tab displays the denied contributors and their associated information.
    </p>

    <h4>Show entries:</h4>
    <p>
        Use this option to choose how many contributors you want to display per page.
    </p>

    <h4>Search:</h4>
    <p>
        Use the search bar to find specific contributors based on their ID, first name, last name, or registration date.
    </p>

    <h4>Columns:</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>ID: Unique identifier for the contributor.</li>
        <li>FirstName: First name of the contributor.</li>
        <li>LastName: Last name of the contributor.</li>
        <li>Register Date: Date when the contributor registered.</li>
        <li>Comments: Additional comments or notes about the contributor.</li>
        <li>Actions: Available actions for the contributor.</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Actions:</h4>
    <p>
        Depending on the context, the available actions may vary. Here is the action explained for the 'Denied Contributors' page:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>
            View SIT Rating: Displays the SIT (System Integration Test) rating for the denied contributor.
        </li>
    </ul>

    <img src="~/images/denied_contributors-1.png" />
</body>
